$TNT From James yahoo

I had a call with Barry at Tenet. He confirmed that if SEC doesn't respond within 30 days they can automatically reapply to NASDAQ. He said their NASDAQ approval still stands and will not have to be redone. He said it is typically a 48 hour turn around to get put back on. The 27th is a Saturday so he said the SEC will likely use Monday as their last day. If there are no new notes (and so far there haven't been any) then they can reapply and should be back on by Wednesday/Thursday next week. If they do have notes they do not have to go through another long approval period. They will just have to accommodate the notes and they will be good to go. He honestly seemed unbothered and confident by the whole thing.
I also asked about the new law firms. He said their lawyers are dealing with it and it doesn't worry them in the slightest as the Grizzly report was complelty discredited.
